Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper focuses on modeling human mobility in social networks and evaluates social-aware protocols for opportunistic routing. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a mobility model for evaluating routing protocols in opportunistic networks. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a model for studying the behavior of social-aware protocols in opportunistic networks. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper proposes a model for studying the behavior of groups in human mobility. 
5. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper discusses the impact of social networks on human mobility and proposes a model for studying it.
